cache/generation/prose_review/prompts/addon-manager.json:446:  "rendered_prompt": "You are reviewing an existing DALi dali-ui application developer guide draft.\nThis is Phase 2.3.5: source-grounded prose review.\n\nPrimary goal:\n- Improve natural-language accuracy and guide flow using repository evidence.\n- Preserve the document's useful structure and examples whenever possible.\n- Do not perform a full rewrite.\n- Keep the revised user-facing guide in en only.\n- Remove Korean, Japanese, Chinese, or other non-English prose from the revised guide.\n\nFeature target:\n- Feature: Addon Manager (addon-manager)\n- Category: platform-integration\n- Guide profile: dali-ui-app\n- Audience: application developers using dali-ui public APIs\n\nReview rules:\n- Review every natural-language paragraph line by line against public headers, implementation files, samples, and UTCs when needed.\n- Accuracy is the first priority. Flow is the second priority.\n- Edit the smallest unit needed: word, sentence, paragraph, or section-local addition/removal.\n- If a word-level change is enough, change only the word.\n- If a sentence-level change is enough, change only the sentence.\n- If an entire paragraph is based on a wrong premise, revise, add, or remove that paragraph.\n- Preserve code blocks when possible.\n- If prose can be corrected to match an already accurate code block, prefer changing prose.\n- If the code block itself makes the prose inaccurate or breaks the guide flow, rewrite only the smallest necessary part of that code block and verify it against public headers/source.\n- Do not invent APIs.\n- Do not add generic filler just to make the document longer.\n- Do not change section structure unless prose_review.allow_section_restructure is true or the current prose is clearly misleading.\n- Prefer localized edits when prose_review.localized_edits_only is true.\n- Preserve code blocks especially when prose_review.preserve_code_blocks is true.\n- Prefer Dali::Ui::View, typed setters, fluent chaining, and view-tree idioms for app-facing guidance.\n- Treat dali-core and dali-adaptor APIs as reference/context unless the feature explicitly requires them.\n\nContext summary:\n{\n  \"content_quality\": {\n    \"overview_style\": \"very_short\",\n    \"require_table_of_contents\": true,\n    \"require_rich_api_examples\": true,\n    \"require_backticks_for_api_names\": true,\n    \"topic_sections_must_be_feature_specific\": true,\n    \"avoid_mechanical_api_listing\": true,\n    \"default_object_model\": \"Use Dali::Ui::View rather than Dali::Actor for app-facing object examples.\",\n    \"guide_assumption\": \"The reader is using dali-ui to build applications.\"\n  },\n  \"prose_review\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"apply_to\": \"all\",\n    \"preserve_code_blocks\": true,\n    \"localized_edits_only\": true,\n    \"allow_section_restructure\": false,\n    \"output_review_report\": true,\n    \"fail_open_on_parse_error\": true\n  },\n  \"surface_usage\": {\n    \"primary_surface\": \"dali-ui\",\n    \"rules\": [\n      \"Use dali-ui symbols as the app-facing API surface.\",\n      \"Use dali-core and dali-adaptor symbols only as setup/background unless the usage pattern explicitly marks them preferred.\",\n      \"Prefer View-based examples over raw Actor object-model examples.\"\n    ],\n    \"symbol_counts\": {\n      \"dali-core\": 37\n    }\n  },\n  \"usage_patterns\": [],\n  \"allowed_symbols_sample\": [\n    {\n      \"display_name\": \"AddOnDispatchTable\",\n      \"header_path\": \"repos/dali-core/dali/integration-api/addon-manager.h\",\n      \"kind\": \"struct\",\n      \"public_api\": true,\n      \"signature\": \"Dali::AddOnDispatchTable\",\n      \"surface\": \"dali-core\",\n      \"symbol_id\": \"Dali::AddOnDispatchTable\",\n      \"usage_scope\": \"primary\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"display_name\": \"AddOnInfo\",\n      \"header_path\": \"repos/dali-core/dali/integration-api/addon-manager.h\",\n      \"kind\": \"struct\",\n